<br>
Take a bottle of Drano. It can kill a child if ingested orally, so they put a label on the bottle, that protects them from lawsuits.<br>
<br>
However, CD's were meant to be played in CD-ROMs. (Or vice versa, being that CD-ROMS are and should be, an acceptable vice for playing CD's.)<br>
<br>
Thus, the company has taken action to WILLFULLY destroy a peice of hardware, to prevent...no...PRE-prevent ripping of tracks. Basically, you're CD ROM is being smashed JUST IN CASE you MIGHT rip a track.<br>
<br>
There is no evidence that Drano has ever created their product so that it will purposefully kill small children. Thats where the difference lies. Assuming this issue comes to a brighter light other than the RTA, my guess is that the company will go to large measures to cover up any evidence that they had knowledge that their product would destroy your CD ROM. <br>
<br>
Because evidence of willfull destruction is all they need. Find that, and the case is sealed up. My prediction is the fact that since stickers were issued along with the CD's, finding that evidence will be easy. <p><a href=http://www.wyrmhole.org/fallenshadows/Database/scripts/character-page.php?charid=5>Kluz</a><br><embed src="http://www.wyrmhole.org/fallenshadows/Flash/kluzsig.swf" quality=high pluginspage="http://www.macromedia.com/shockwave/download/index.cgi?P1_Prod_Version=ShockwaveFlash" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="200" height="150"></embed><br><a href=http://www.fallenshadows.cjb.net>Fallen Shadows</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unenyadevichier.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nenya deVichier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/9/02 7:21:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=720.topic&index=28>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Copy Protections</span><hr size=1> Yes it does work.. I have been using this method of bypassing the protection process for a while now.. The best pens I have found are the 'Dry Wipe' board markers as they can be wiped off with very little effort and leave no trace behind.<br>
